comment_data.body:
Why specifically would it tickle close callbacks? Did you mean just to run the loop once to execute any pending callbacks which _may_ be close callbacks? If so, why wouldn't the `uv_run` call below also do this?

For context luv doesn't do this so just trying to understand the differences. For reference luv just does:

```c
  // Call uv_close on every active handle
  uv_walk(loop, walk_cb, NULL);
  // Run the event loop until all handles are successfully closed
  while (uv_loop_close(loop)) {
    uv_run(loop, UV_RUN_DEFAULT);
  }
```

