> It would, but that may not be reached, depending on wait.

Oh so we can simplify this further then with something like?

```c
  if (!wait) {
    // Run the loop to run any pending callbacks (which may then free memory).
    // Use UV_RUN_NOWAIT to avoid a hang. #11820
    uv_run(loop, UV_RUN_NOWAIT);
    uv_loop_close(loop);
    return true;
  }
```

> luv doesn't care about hangs, whereas we need to exit quickly.

Shouldn't it? If our code is _better_ than theirs, then I'd be happy to port some of it over. We use their loop handling for our Lua threads.

