comment_data.body:
I guess so, but I'm not sure if it's significant.

Now we have:
```c
 // Run the event loop until all handles are successfully closed
  while (uv_loop_close(loop)) {
    uv_run(loop, UV_RUN_DEFAULT);
    uint64_t elapsed_s = (os_hrtime() - start) / 1000000000;  // seconds
    if (elapsed_s >= 2) {
      // Some libuv resource was not correctly deref'd. Log and bail.
      ELOG("uv_loop_close() hang?");
      log_uv_handles(loop);
      return false;
    }
  }
  return true;
```

Which is pretty similar to what luv does, and is a lot easier to follow.

I guess elapsed is checked slightly different. I can move that code above `uv_run` which makes it closer to was there before.

